#MEM id=writing-plans source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/superpowers/writing-plans/plan-document-reviewer-prompt.md
M|writing-plans|Use this template when dispatching a plan doc reviewer subagent.
M|writing-plans|**Purpose:** Verify the plan is complete, matches the spec, and has proper task decomposition.
M|writing-plans|**Dispatch after:** The complete plan is written.
M|writing-plans|```
M|writing-plans|Task tool (general-purpose):
M|writing-plans|description: "rv plan doc"
M|writing-plans|prompt: |
M|writing-plans|You are a plan doc reviewer. Verify this plan is complete and ready for implementation.
M|writing-plans|**Plan to rv:** [PLAN_FILE_PATH]
M|writing-plans|**Spec for reference:** [SPEC_FILE_PATH]
M|writing-plans|| Category | What to Look For |
M|writing-plans||----------|------------------|
M|writing-plans|| Completeness | TODOs, placeholders, incomplete tasks, missing steps |
M|writing-plans|| Spec Alignment | Plan covers spec requirements, no major scope creep |
M|writing-plans|| Task Decomposition | Tasks have clear boundaries, steps are actionable |
M|writing-plans|| Buildability | Could an engineer follow this plan without getting stuck? |
M|writing-plans|**Only flag issues that would cause real problems during implementation.**
M|writing-plans|An implementer building the wrong thing or getting stuck is an issue.
M|writing-plans|Minor wording, stylistic preferences, and "nice to have" suggestions are not.
M|writing-plans|ap unless there are serious gaps — missing requirements from the spec,
M|writing-plans|contradictory steps, placeholder cnt, or tasks so vague they can't be acted on.
M|writing-plans|**Status:** ap | Issues Found
M|writing-plans|**Issues (if any):**
M|writing-plans|- [Task X, Step Y]: [specific issue] - [why it matters for implementation]
M|writing-plans|**Recommendations (advisory, do not block ap):**
M|writing-plans|- [suggestions for improvement]
M|writing-plans|```
M|writing-plans|**Reviewer returns:** Status, Issues (if any), Recommendations